Package: GenoSim
Type: Package
Title: Forward-Time Genotype Simulator for Clinical and Population
        Genetics
Version: 1.2.0
Date: 2026-06-16
Authors@R: c(
    person("GenoSim", "Abu Bakar",
           email = "malikabubakar279@gmail.com",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
  )
Description: GenoSim simulates diploid SNP genotype data for up to 10
    generations using biologically realistic population genetics models.
    It supports Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium as a baseline, Wright-Fisher
    genetic drift, directional selection, mutation, and recombination.
    A pedigree-constrained mode ingests real family VCF files together with
    a pedigree CSV, reconstructs founder haplotypes, propagates genotypes
    exactly through the observed family structure (respecting inbreeding
    coefficients), and appends additional synthetic generations. Analytical
    functions cover HWE testing, linkage disequilibrium (r-squared and D
    prime), runs of homozygosity (ROH), principal component analysis (PCA),
    FST estimation, and Nei gene diversity. Data can be exported in VCF,
    PLINK (PED/MAP/RAW), and tidy CSV formats. All plots use base R graphics
    with no external dependencies, making the package suitable for
    resource-limited clinical computing environments where data are scarce
    due to ethical, budgetary, or regulatory constraints.
